HOW IS NEW HAVEN?

We’re one week in with the new students and so far things seem to be going safely in New Haven. Our tests are up significantly compared to last week and last month, and the percent share positive is down. New Cases may seem high today; however, the testing volume and percent share positive speak for themselves here and the higher number is likely due to the weekend. It will be interesting to see if these numbers evolve at all over the coming week to see if the new students are a factor, but what will give a better sense of the handle Yale has on the situation will be about a month from now when social distance fatigue begins to set in. For now though, things seem safe.
